Following the recommendation of the United Nations Secretary-General, after consultation with Member States, the General Assembly has extended the tenure of the Executive Director of the United Nations Human Settlements Programme (UN-Habitat), Maimunah Mohd Sharif to another two years, beginning  January 20, 2022, to 19 January 2024. Before becoming Executive Director, Sharif served as Mayor of Penang in Malaysia and was President of the Malaysian Association of Local Authorities (MALA). A town planner by profession, Sharif was Co-President of United Cities and Local Government for Asia Pacific (UCLG-ASPAC). She was also elected to represent South East Asia in the Global Executive Committee of ICLEI (Local Government for Sustainability). Since joining the United Nations in 2018, Sharif has re-positioned UN-Habitat as a thought leader in sustainable urbanisation.  She is the Co-Chair of the Secretary-Generalâ€™s Task Force on the Future of Cities and Co-Chair of the Local 2030 Coalition. 